    "We will take a slight liberty in notation to defineQ(µ I):= Σ d 2 z e -2ρ(z)-iσ(z)-iH(z) Q(z)µ I (z).The number of insertions of each b-ghost can be determined from the ghost charge.",
    "The result is that (g -1) copies of b(µ I) and (n + 2g -2) copies of Q(µ I) should be inserted, as explained in appendix B.",
    "We will implicitly assume this is the case in what follows.foot_15 JHEP04(2024)048The states V w m 1,m 2 are specified by the free field realisation of psu(1, 1|2) 1.",
    "In performing the quotient of (2.5), we explicitly gauged away Z but found that a second U(1) current Y decoupled from the theory.",
    "We treat Y 0 as a picture and only consider physical correlators that have an overall vanishing Y 0 eigenvalue."
